This may not be an actual typeface, then.. It rather looks like a custom raw / rough / grunge / remixed / filtered version, because none of the 'O's, for example, looks the same..   
_( Maybe you could use, and abuse, a ultra condensed version of ' [Univers](http://web.archive.org/web/20050518053158/http:/www.linotype.com/1560/univers-family.html)' or a compressed version of ' [Helvetica](http://web.archive.org/web/20050518053158/http:/www.linotype.com/526/helvetica-family.html)' with various filters to imitate this kind of 'style'.. )_
